english:
  title: Reflections on My Heart
  author: Sung Seok-yeon
  language: eng
  text: |-
    On the day when flesh and blood must part,
    I walk alone through an empty city.
    Near my tears, the yellow warbler draws close,
    And within my sorrow, white hairs spring forth.

    Old age already hastens the year to its end,
    Yet my name still contends with worldly gain.
    Who knows that Heaven has watchful eyes—
    That it sees, one by one, the true hearts of men.
  footnotes:
    - The poem reflects on aging, separation from loved ones, and the contrast between ambition and the inevitable approach of death. The speaker questions whether Heaven truly observes human nature and moral character.
